The paper discusses network security and defense techniques, which falls under the category of "Computer Science and Game Theory" (cs.GT) and "Computer Science and Cryptography and Security" (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on Moving Target Defense (MTD) techniques, which are used to dynamically re-configure network systems to reduce the effectiveness of cyber attacks. This falls under the category of "Computer Science and Networking and Internet Architecture" (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of artificial intelligence techniques for decision making in MTDs, which falls under the category of "Computer Science and Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) and "Computer Science and Systems and Control" (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation and practicality of MTDs, which falls under the category of "Computer Science and Software Engineering" (cs.SE).
